text:
To be fair dude, I don't think Game Arts are truly dead or anything. Just two weeks ago they released Ragnarok Odyssey Ace into Europe shelves for PS3 and PS Vita. However , there does seem to be a big gap between their last release: Dokuro, and the re-releases of Ragnarok Odyssey. So I'm hoping they can get back on their feet soon and develop more games.

Because I agree with you, their games are like no other in terms of personality and character. This game was enough to prove that to me (great choice of music by the way). Good idea in replaying this game too! Personally, it's far superior to Grandia II in many ways, though Grandia II is still a great title.
